    "Conversely, closed-source models may offer better professional support, user interfaces, and performance, but confine their development within proprietary boundaries, thus restricting their availability and flexibility.Parameter Size and Computational Complexity.",
    "Parameter size is a pivotal factor in the selection of medical LLMs.",
    "Large models like MedPaLM (540 billion parameters) offer in-depth understanding and complex reasoning capabilities.",
    "However, their deployment demands substantial resources, making them less feasible for constrained environments.",
    "Conversely, smaller models in the 7B-13B range, such as MedAlpaca and AlpaCare, strike a balance between efficiency and effectiveness, facilitating easier deployment.Domains, Modality, Language and Usage."
